</taxonomicNameLabel>
Male genitalia, holotype.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="DF59C4B8FFE97D22899FFD6E0699E4D4" box="[151,920,664,686]" pageId="7" pageNumber="588">
<paragraph id="8B999430FFE97D22899FFD6E0699E4D4" blockId="7.[151,920,664,686]" box="[151,920,664,686]" pageId="7" pageNumber="588">
<emphasis id="B9524822FFE97D22899FFD6E0419E4D7" bold="true" box="[151,280,664,686]" pageId="7" pageNumber="588">FIGURE 31</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C26EFB3FFE97D22882DFD6F04ADE4D4" authority="Duarte, 2017" authorityName="Duarte" authorityYear="2017" box="[293,428,664,686]" class="Insecta" family="Hepialidae" genus="Limyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="588" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silvai" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9524822FFE97D22882DFD6F04ADE4D4" box="[293,428,664,686]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="588">
Limyra 
<taxonomicName id="4C26EFB3FFE97D22887DFD6E04ADE4D4" box="[373,428,664,686]" pageId="7" pageNumber="588" rank="species" species="silvai" status="sp. nov.">silvai</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A261F559FFE97D2288BAFD6E0703E4D7" box="[434,514,664,685]" pageId="7" pageNumber="588" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B9524822FFE97D2288BAFD6E0703E4D7" bold="true" box="[434,514,664,685]" pageId="7" pageNumber="588">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
Male (left) and female (right) venation.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8B999430FFE97D2289CFFD2306EAE56B" blockId="7.[151,1437,725,1758]" pageId="7" pageNumber="588">
<emphasis id="B9524822FFE97D2289CFFD230420E494" box="[199,289,725,750]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="588">Thorax:</emphasis>
Legs: distitarsus as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C26EFB3FFE97D228B3AFD230781E494" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1856" box="[562,640,725,750]" class="Insecta" family="Hepialidae" genus="Cibyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="588" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9524822FFE97D228B3AFD230781E494" box="[562,640,725,750]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="588">Cibyra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Venation of fore- and hindwings as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C26EFB3FFE97D228D5DFD2301A2E494" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1856" box="[1109,1187,725,750]" class="Insecta" family="Hepialidae" genus="Cibyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="588" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9524822FFE97D228D5DFD2301A2E494" box="[1109,1187,725,750]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="588">Cibyra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but in forewing Sc1 vestigial; in hindwing CuP vestigial, M2 complete and 2A present (
<figureCitation id="131D88B5FFE97D228A83FD0F06DFE56B" box="[907,990,761,786]" captionStart="FIGURE 31" captionStartId="7.[151,250,664,686]" captionText="FIGURE 31. Limyra silvai sp. nov. Male (left) and female (right) venation." pageId="7" pageNumber="588">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B999430FFE97D2289CFFCEB0775E54C" blockId="7.[151,1437,725,1758]" box="[199,628,797,822]" pageId="7" pageNumber="588">
<emphasis id="B9524822FFE97D2289CFFCEB0430E54C" box="[199,305,797,822]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="588">Abdomen</emphasis>
: Sternum VIII membranous.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B999430FFE97D2289CFFCB70656E5BC" blockId="7.[151,1437,725,1758]" pageId="7" pageNumber="588">
<emphasis id="B9524822FFE97D2289CFFCB7046AE520" box="[199,363,833,858]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="588">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="131D88B5FFE97D228871FCB704FBE520" box="[377,506,833,858]" captionStart="FIGURES 22 − 29" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1386,1409]" captionTargetBox="[152,1430,207,1365]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,193,1365]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 22 − 29. Limyra silvai sp. nov. 22. Male abdomen (holotype), upper dorsal, lower ventral view. 23 − 25. Male genitalia (holotype): 23, ventral view; 24, lateral view; 25, anterior view (internal), fultura superior (arrow). 26 − 27. Female abdomen (MZSP 14.404). 26, upper dorsal, lower ventral view; 27, tergum and sternum VII and VIII (tergum VIII membranous), sternum VIII (arrow). 28 − 29. Female genitalia (MZSP 14.404). 28, lateral view; 29, posterior view. Scale bar = 1 mm, except Figs 22 and 26 = 1 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/998530/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="588">Figs 23–25</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="131D88B5FFE97D228B0EFCB70727E523" box="[518,550,833,857]" captionStart="FIGURE 30" captionStartId="6.[151,250,2004,2026]" captionText="FIGURE 30. Limyra silvai sp. nov. Male genitalia, holotype." pageId="7" pageNumber="588">30</figureCitation>
). Tegumen mostly fused to the pseudotegumen, ventral portion articulated with saccus. Saccus convex and in two fused parts. Tergal lobes softly sclerotized, resting on against the pseudotegumen. Pseudotegumen dorsally and ventrally unfused. Fultura superior present. Valvae slightly setose. Phallus membranous and when everted the vesica as a bladder.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B999430FFE97D2289CFFC2706CDE590" blockId="7.[151,1437,725,1758]" box="[199,972,977,1002]" pageId="7" pageNumber="588">
<emphasis id="B9524822FFE97D2289CFFC27041DE590" box="[199,284,977,1002]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="588">Female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="131D88B5FFE97D228821FC2704AAE590" box="[297,427,977,1002]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 − 15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1375,1398]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,628,1354]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,628,1354]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 11 − 15. Limyra silvai sp. nov. 11, male holotype, dorsal view; 12, male holotype, ventral view; 13, male paratype, dorsal view (MZSP 14.403); 14, female paratype, dorsal view (MZSP 14.404); 15, female paratype, ventral view (MZSP 14.404). Scale bar = 1 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/998526/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="588">Figs 14, 15</figureCitation>
). Only differences from the male are mentioned.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B999430FFE97D2289CFFC03014FE22F" blockId="7.[151,1437,725,1758]" pageId="7" pageNumber="588">
<emphasis id="B9524822FFE97D2289CFFC030405E274" box="[199,260,1013,1038]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="588">Head</emphasis>
: clypeus anteriorly and medially projected, glabrous and slightly differentiated from the frons. Labial palpus one-segmented. Antenna bipectinate with rami arising from a slight projection at the mid length of the antennomere, sensilla trichodea reduced in size and quantity, sensilla caetica present.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B999430FFE97D2289CFFB97017CE203" blockId="7.[151,1437,725,1758]" box="[199,1149,1121,1146]" pageId="7" pageNumber="588">
<emphasis id="B9524822FFE97D2289CFFB97041EE200" box="[199,287,1121,1146]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="588">Thorax.</emphasis>
Venation of fore- and hindwings as in male, but hindwing with 3A (
<figureCitation id="131D88B5FFE97D228D15FB970171E203" box="[1053,1136,1121,1146]" captionStart="FIGURE 31" captionStartId="7.[151,250,664,686]" captionText="FIGURE 31. Limyra silvai sp. nov. Male (left) and female (right) venation." pageId="7" pageNumber="588">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B999430FFE97D2289CFFB730695E2B8" blockId="7.[151,1437,725,1758]" pageId="7" pageNumber="588">
<emphasis id="B9524822FFE97D2289CFFB730430E2E4" box="[199,305,1157,1182]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="588">Abdomen</emphasis>
: tergum VIII as a thick membrane; sternum VIII compound as two lateral, slightly sclerotized, and semi-circular plates linked by a narrow sclerotized ridge posteriorly.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B999430FFE97D2289CFFB3B0659E328" blockId="7.[151,1437,725,1758]" pageId="7" pageNumber="588">
<emphasis id="B9524822FFE97D2289CFFB3B0486E29C" box="[199,391,1229,1254]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="588">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="131D88B5FFE97D22889EFB3B071AE29C" box="[406,539,1229,1254]" captionStart="FIGURES 22 − 29" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1386,1409]" captionTargetBox="[152,1430,207,1365]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,193,1365]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 22 − 29. Limyra silvai sp. nov. 22. Male abdomen (holotype), upper dorsal, lower ventral view. 23 − 25. Male genitalia (holotype): 23, ventral view; 24, lateral view; 25, anterior view (internal), fultura superior (arrow). 26 − 27. Female abdomen (MZSP 14.404). 26, upper dorsal, lower ventral view; 27, tergum and sternum VII and VIII (tergum VIII membranous), sternum VIII (arrow). 28 − 29. Female genitalia (MZSP 14.404). 28, lateral view; 29, posterior view. Scale bar = 1 mm, except Figs 22 and 26 = 1 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/998530/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="588">Figs 28, 29</figureCitation>
). Anal papillae tapered, projected posteriorly. Lamella antevaginalis compound mainly by two processes separated meso-anteriorly that extends ventro-posteriorly fusing to a mesal process, thus forming a depression between both structures. Antrum situated anterior to the lamella. Subanal plate slightly sclerotized. Ductus bursae tube-like; corpus bursae cylindrical.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33CC7BBFFE97D2289CFFAAB0651E07C" pageId="7" pageNumber="588" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B999430FFE97D2289CFFAAB0651E07C" blockId="7.[151,1437,725,1758]" pageId="7" pageNumber="588">
<emphasis id="B9524822FFE97D2289CFFAAB0447E30C" bold="true" box="[199,326,1373,1398]" pageId="7" pageNumber="588">Etymology</emphasis>
. While forming the generic name 
<taxonomicName id="4C26EFB3FFE97D228BC6FAA8061EE30F" authority="Duarte, 2017" authorityName="Duarte" authorityYear="2017" box="[718,799,1374,1397]" class="Insecta" family="Hepialidae" genus="Limyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="588" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9524822FFE97D228BC6FAA8061EE30F" box="[718,799,1374,1397]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="588">Limyra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
we follow the tradition of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB7E9C1FFE97D228D5AFAAB01F6E30C" author="Walker, F." box="[1106,1271,1373,1398]" journalOrPublisher="Lepidoptera Heterocera. London (Trustees of BMNH)" pageId="7" pageNumber="588" pagination="1509" part="4" refString="Walker, F. (1856) List of the specimens of lepidopterous insects in the collection of the British Museum. Part VII. Lepidoptera Heterocera. London (Trustees of BMNH), [4] pp. + pp. [1509] - 1808." title="List of the specimens of lepidopterous insects in the collection of the British Museum. Part VII" type="journal article" year="1856">Walker (1856)</bibRefCitation>
, who gave the generic name 
<taxonomicName id="4C26EFB3FFE97D22883EFA770485E3E0" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1856" box="[310,388,1409,1434]" class="Insecta" family="Hepialidae" genus="Cibyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="588" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9524822FFE97D22883EFA770485E3E0" box="[310,388,1409,1434]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="588">Cibyra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for the genus of moths distributed in South America. We suppose that the name of the antic town Κιβυρα served as an inspiration. The name of the new genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C26EFB3FFE97D228A8FFA5006D9E3C7" authority="Duarte, 2017" authorityName="Duarte" authorityYear="2017" box="[903,984,1446,1469]" class="Insecta" family="Hepialidae" genus="Limyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="588" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9524822FFE97D228A8FFA5006D9E3C7" box="[903,984,1446,1469]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="588">Limyra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also derives from the name of the small antic city (in Greek Λιµύρα) in Lycia on the southern coast of 
<collectingCountry id="F331D4A0FFE97D228A6AFA3F06E7E398" box="[866,998,1481,1506]" name="Turkey" pageId="7" pageNumber="588">Asia Minor</collectingCountry>
, on the Limyrus River. Nowadays this place are ruins in 
<collectingCountry id="F331D4A0FFE97D228856FA1B04B1E07C" box="[350,432,1517,1542]" name="Turkey" pageId="7" pageNumber="588">Turkey</collectingCountry>
. The gender of the name is feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33CC7BBFFE97D2289CFF9E7072DE0A4" pageId="7" pageNumber="588" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B999430FFE97D2289CFF9E7072DE0A4" blockId="7.[151,1437,725,1758]" pageId="7" pageNumber="588">
<emphasis id="B9524822FFE97D2289CFF9E70435E050" bold="true" box="[199,308,1553,1578]" pageId="7" pageNumber="588">Remarks</emphasis>
. The presence of 
<taxonomicName id="4C26EFB3FFE97D2288F6F9E4074EE053" authority="Duarte, 2017" authorityName="Duarte" authorityYear="2017" box="[510,591,1554,1577]" class="Insecta" family="Hepialidae" genus="Limyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="588" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9524822FFE97D2288F6F9E4074EE053" box="[510,591,1554,1577]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="588">Limyra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A261F559FFE97D228B5FF9E707C0E050" box="[599,705,1553,1578]" pageId="7" pageNumber="588" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9524822FFE97D228B5FF9E707C0E050" bold="true" box="[599,705,1553,1578]" pageId="7" pageNumber="588">gen. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
in southern 
<collectingCountry id="F331D4A0FFE97D228A46F9E70693E050" box="[846,914,1553,1578]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="588">Brazil</collectingCountry>
is surprising since no other matching taxon is so far known. The presence of posterior lateral knob (not strongly developed), a broad intermediate connection between the tergosternal bar, the lateral ridge and a broken anterior margin at the tergosternal connection, along with a very close parallel position between the outer hindwing Sc and R veins support the inclusion of 
<taxonomicName id="4C26EFB3FFE97D228C1BF9880065E0EF" authority="Duarte, 2017" authorityName="Duarte" authorityYear="2017" box="[1299,1380,1662,1685]" class="Insecta" family="Hepialidae" genus="Limyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="588" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9524822FFE97D228C1BF9880065E0EF" box="[1299,1380,1662,1685]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="588">Limyra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A261F559FFE97D228C63F98B05C9E0C0" pageId="7" pageNumber="588" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9524822FFE97D228C63F98B05C9E0C0" bold="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="588">gen. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
within the 'cibyrine' cluster of genera (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB7E9C1FFE97D228B91F9570634E0C3" author="Grehan, J. R" box="[665,821,1697,1722]" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the Buffalo Society of Natural Sciences" pageId="7" pageNumber="588" pagination="1 - 30" part="42" refString="Grehan, J. R (2012) Morphological evidence for phylogenetic relationships within the Hepialidae (Lepidoptera: Exoporia). Bulletin of the Buffalo Society of Natural Sciences, 42, 1 - 30." title="Morphological evidence for phylogenetic relationships within the Hepialidae (Lepidoptera: Exoporia)" type="journal article" year="2012">Grehan 2012</bibRefCitation>
). Further investigation will be necessary for a better understanding of such relationships.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
